    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-gui-in-eclipse-on-mac-cannot-display-html-or-access-local-files/qaq-p/13731371</id>
    <title>SAP GUI in Eclipse on Mac cannot display HTML or access local files</title>
    <updated>2024-06-14T17:27:28.057000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>pokrakam</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/524</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I'm using Java GUI on Mac. Standalone it works fine. Eclipse ADT native functionality also works fine.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The problem is when a SapGUI session is opened inside Eclipse. Anything with HTML or needing local file access doesn't work. For example, downloading a file fails:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="pokrakam_0-1718378353104.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/123852i9EE151AA993179A7/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="pokrakam_0-1718378353104.png" alt="pokrakam_0-1718378353104.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any transactions or popup windows that use HTML also fail. For example a popup generated by POPUP_TO_CONFIRM will load the popup, but the text content is rendered using HTML and fails:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="pokrakam_1-1718378449710.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/123853i50B8FFD47567D0CD/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="pokrakam_1-1718378449710.png" alt="pokrakam_1-1718378449710.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The same popup from a standalone Java GUI session (not inside Eclipse) works fine:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="pokrakam_2-1718378550752.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/123854i1638E3B91F5D5F3F/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="pokrakam_2-1718378550752.png" alt="pokrakam_2-1718378550752.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I'm guessing it's something to do with local/eclipse/java authorizations, but I've done all I can think of. Eclipse and SAP GUI have full disk access. The SAP system is fully trusted.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I've also reinstalled both Eclipse and SAP GUI numerous times, today upgraded to the latest Eclipse 2024-06 and still have the issue. I've had to set up JavaFX manually to get SAPGUI to run inside eclipse, also with various versions - now on 21.0.3&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Edit: I did a little more digging and the symptoms all seem to indicate the system's trust level is defaulted to something other than highest (probably the default 3). I can't see anywhere when adding a project that I can specify this. And I'm guessing when launching an internal SAPGUI session it will bypass whatever I've configured in the SAPLogon app.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any ideas?&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-gui-in-eclipse-on-mac-cannot-display-html-or-access-local-files/qaq-p/13731371"/>
    <published>2024-06-14T17:27:28.057000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
