      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/217904</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi Experts,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I'm developing a Fiori Elements app using RAP in the SAP BTP ABAP environment. This application includes Value Helps with additionalBinding. However, I have noticed that sometimes changes to the additionalBinding for a Value Help are not reflected on the frontend.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Upon investigation, I discovered that these Value Helps, which are based on other CDS Views, make a metadata call the first time they are invoked on the frontend.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="jayme_alonso_0-1718620428870.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/124365iC76FAC1AC0F8702F/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="jayme_alonso_0-1718620428870.png" alt="jayme_alonso_0-1718620428870.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;This metadata, separate from the main Fiori Elements metadata, contains the additionalBinding as a Value Help input parameter. Unfortunately, it does not update according to the changes made in the CDS.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="jayme_alonso_1-1718627735074.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/124447iC8F37BBF3D077A64/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="jayme_alonso_1-1718627735074.png" alt="jayme_alonso_1-1718627735074.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Eventually, the metadata updates after modifying the metadata extension object in other places. This issue is difficult to consistently replicate.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I suspect this might be a caching problem on the backend. In an on-premise system, we could clear the backend cache directly by running a report. However, in BTP, there seems to be no straightforward way to do this. How can I check if the cache is the problem, and how can I invalidate it to update this metadata on the frontend?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thanks!&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/btp-abap-environment-additionalbinding-metadata-cache/qaq-p/13733296"/>
    <published>2024-06-17T14:45:19.457000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
